## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-225">O <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> método ler no máximo `count` bytes atuais de fluxo e armazená-los na `buffer` começando em `offset`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-225">The <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> method read a maximum of `count` bytes from the current stream and store them in `buffer` beginning at `offset`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-226">Avança a posição atual dentro do fluxo pelo número de bytes lido; No entanto, se ocorrer uma exceção, a posição atual dentro do fluxo permanecerá inalterada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-226">The current position within the stream is advanced by the number of bytes read; however, if an exception occurs, the current position within the stream remains unchanged.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-227"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> Retorna o número de bytes lidos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-227"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> returns the number of bytes read.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-228">O valor de retorno é zero somente se a posição no momento está no final do fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-228">The return value is zero only if the position is currently at the end of the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-229"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> será bloqueada até que pelo menos um byte de dados podem ser lidos, que não há dados disponíveis.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-229"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> will block until at least one byte of data can be read, in the event that no data is available.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-230"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> Retorna 0 somente quando o final do arquivo foi atingido.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-230"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> returns 0 only when the end of the file has been reached.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-231"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> está livre para retornar menos bytes que solicitado, mesmo se o final do fluxo não foi atingido.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-231"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> is free to return fewer bytes than requested even if the end of the stream has not been reached.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-232">Qualquer tentativa de acessar um fechados <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> usando o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> ou <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A> métodos reabre um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> transmitir automaticamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-232">Any attempt to access a closed <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> using the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> or <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A> methods reopens an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> stream automatically.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-233">O exemplo c# a seguir pressupõe que a este esquema em uma tabela do Oracle:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-233">The following C# example assumes this schema in an Oracle table:</span></span>  
  
```  
(col1 number, col2 BFILE)  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-234">O exemplo demonstra como usar o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> e <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A> métodos para acessar um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> objeto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-234">The example demonstrates using the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> and <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A> methods to access an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> object.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
byte[] buffer = new byte[100];  
OracleDataReader dataReader = command.ExecuteReader();  
using (dataReader) {  
    if (dataReader.Read()) {  
            OracleBFile BFile = dataReader.GetOracleBFile(1);  
        using (BFile) {  
            BFile.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin);  
            BFile.Read(buffer, 0, 100);  
        }  
    }  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-248">Se `offset` for negativo, a nova posição é necessária para preceder a posição especificada pela `origin` pelo número de bytes especificado por `offset`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-248">If `offset` is negative, the new position is required to precede the position specified by `origin` by the number of bytes specified by `offset`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-249">Se `offset` for zero, a nova posição é necessária para ser a posição especificada pela `origin`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-249">If `offset` is zero, the new position is required to be the position specified by `origin`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="88034-250">Se `offset` for positivo, a nova posição é necessária para seguir a posição especificada pela `origin` pelo número de bytes especificado por `offset`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-250">If `offset` is positive, the new position is required to follow the position specified by `origin` by the number of bytes specified by `offset`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-251">Não há suporte para a busca em qualquer local além do comprimento do fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-251">Seeking to any location beyond the length of the stream is not supported.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-252">Qualquer tentativa de acessar um fechados <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> usando o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> ou <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A> métodos reabre um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> transmitir automaticamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-252">Any attempt to access a closed <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> using the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Read%2A> or <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile.Seek%2A> methods reopens an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> stream automatically.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="88034-253">O exemplo c# a seguir pressupõe que a este esquema em uma tabela do Oracle:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="88034-253">The following C# example assumes this schema in an Oracle table:</span></span>  
  
```  
(col1 number, col2 BFILE)  
